==English==

===Letter===
'''Æ'''  '''æ'''

# A ligature of a and e, usually found in words of Greek origin, though Latin is not uncommon. In US English, this is usually (but not always) replaced with "e" when it has the sound /ɛ/ (SAMPA /E/) or /iː/ (SAMPA /i:/) sound, but not when it makes a different sound, as in "formulæ." In both UK and US English, when "æ" marks the plural of words ending in ''-a'', it is written as two letters ("ae"), although the ligature is used in older texts written in UK English.<!--All this is rather encyclopedic and should really be in Wikipedia if it is not already-->

===Proper noun===
'''Æ'''

# [[pseudonym|Pseudonym]] for Irish writer, [[w:George William Russell|George William Russell]] 

